post_text:
It is that time a year again... Our annual FUNdraiser.

We could not do this without our amazing sponsors.

The 1st sponsor we are highlighting is very near and dear to our community.
Subway in Polk City (Jodi and Kathy Bermel)
Not only do they contribute so much with this fundraiser every year, they bring subway for the high school athletes on game days and countless other things around our community.
Thank you Bermels for all you do!!!

-Sheila Wallace

PO Box 366
Granger, Iowa 50109

Thank you!
#WGstrong

post_text:
Happy Wednesday Hawks! Before the end of the school year the PTO wants to recognize our hard working volunteers for their support, generosity, and commitment to WG students and staff, and we're kicking off this series with one of our favorites, Paula Mai Genkinger!

This week, Paula is showing her appreciation for our teachers by treating them to a spa day! But her commitment to WG doesn't stop there. She also coordinates Junior Achievement and so much more, but we'll let Paula speak for herself!

Thanks Mama! WG is better because of you!

Stay tuned for more videos of PTO volunteer recognition as the school year winds down, and from all of us at the PTO, thank you, thank you, thank you!

Today we officially kicked off our annual WG Elementary PTO Fundraiser. The funds raised all go directly back to the school in the form of field trips, $ for each classroom, technology, Scholastic weekly readers, reading programs, and so much more. This year we have a goal to raise enough to purchase a new piece of playground equipment for the ELC in addition to everything else. Feel free to message the PTO here or at wgelementarypto@gmail.com with any questions.

Attached are the documents that went home with each student today in their Friday Folders.
